  "body_html": "The table below lists the major dermatome landmarks:<br /><br /><div class=\"table-responsive\"><table class = \"tlarge table table-striped table-bordered\"  data-role=\"table\" id=\"tableid1\" ><thead><tr><th><b>Nerve root</b></th><th><b>Landmark</b></th><th><b>Mnemonics</b></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>C2</td><td>Posterior half of the skull (cap)</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>C3</td><td>High turtleneck shirt</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>C4</td><td>Low-collar shirt</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>C5, C6</td><td>Thumb + index finger</td><td><div class='alert alert-warning'>Make a 6 with your left hand by touching the tip of the thumb & index finger together - C6</div></td></tr><tr><td>C7</td><td>Middle finger + palm of hand</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>C8</td><td>Ring + little finger</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>T4</td><td>Nipples</td><td><div class='alert alert-warning'>T4 at the Teat Pore</div></td></tr><tr><td>T5</td><td>Inframammary fold</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>T6</td><td>Xiphoid process</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>T10</td><td>Umbilicus</td><td><div class='alert alert-warning'>BellybuT-TEN</div></td></tr><tr><td>L1</td><td>Inguinal ligament</td><td><div class='alert alert-warning'>L for ligament, 1 for 1nguinal </div></td></tr><tr><td>L4</td><td>Knee caps</td><td><div class='alert alert-warning'>Down on aLL fours - L4</div></td></tr><tr><td>L5</td><td>Big toe, dorsum of foot (except lateral aspect)</td><td><div class='alert alert-warning'>L5 = Largest of the 5 toes</div></td></tr><tr><td>S1</td><td>Lateral foot, small toe</td><td><div class='alert alert-warning'>S1 = the smallest one</div></td></tr><tr><td>S2, S3</td><td>Genitalia</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_FRCEMtutor/pdd009b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_FRCEMtutor/pdd009.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td v